From 217f2b4a950900e2188481a4d72781158014426f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <bramar@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 11 Jul 2025 21:15:56 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: mac80211: Fix to prevent access to unreserved channel context

Issue: Crash seen during channel switch.

Reason: Attempt to access an unreserved channel context results
in a crash during channel switch.

Fix: If the reserved flag is set and a link has not reserved a
channel context, that link shall be excluded from the channel
switch procedure.

Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <bramar@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/chan.c | 12 +++++++++---
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/net/mac80211/chan.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/chan.c
@@ -477,9 +477,12 @@ static void ieee80211_chan_bw_change(str
 			if (!link_sta)
 				continue;
 
-			if (reserved)
-				new_chandef = &link->reserved.oper;
-			else
+			if (reserved) {
+				if (!link->reserved_chanctx)
+					continue;
+				else
+					new_chandef = &link->reserved.oper;
+			} else
 				new_chandef = &link_conf->chanreq.oper;
 
 			new_sta_bw = _ieee80211_sta_cur_vht_bw(link_sta,
